# Force binary handling regardless of core.autocrlf — without this, git's
# content-sniffing heuristic can classify a text-safe binary format (like our
# hand-built minimal PDF, which is pure ASCII) as text and normalize LF to
# CRLF on checkout. That shifts every byte offset in a PDF's xref table and
# silently corrupts the file. Never let git guess for these.
*.pdf -text
*.png -text
*.jpg -text
*.jpeg -text
*.gif -text
*.webp -text
*.ico -text
*.woff -text
*.woff2 -text
*.ttf -text
*.otf -text
